              <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="234.0" prefWidth="527.0">
                     <children>
                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="44.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The Effort Log Editor is the much more specific way to edit a project. The console is by far the easiest way to create a project, however, the editor is neccessary when editing the current entry and making sure all data is correct. Make sure an entry is selected to edit it or click &quot;clear this effort log.&quot; When modifying a log, make sure to select the date, start time, stop time, life cycle step, and effort category. Once these options are selected, clock update this entry. There are also more specific options of clicking delete the current log entry, split this entry into two entries, and proceed to the effort log console." wrappingWidth="500.0">
                           <font>
                              <Font size="14.0" />
                           </font>
                        </Text>
                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="198.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="An important note is that if a user forgets to make a log, make a quick log and then update it with the correct info." wrappingWidth="500.0">
