              <content>
                <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                     <children>
                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="43.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The Defect Console is important for assuring that the data entered is correct. The idea of the Defect Console is that when wrong information is added, it can not only be accounted for but also identified. This is done by selecting the project and the defect, but also more importantly then sleecting the current defect attributes and describing the the defect. The user must then select the step when injected, the step when removed, and finally the defect category. From there, if all info is correct, select &quot;update the current defect,&quot; and otherwise select &quot;delete the current defect&quot;" wrappingWidth="500.0">
                           <font>
                              <Font size="14.0" />
                           </font>
                        </Text>
                     </children>
                  </AnchorPane>
              </content>
            </Tab>
