                <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                     <children>
                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="38.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The EffortLogger Definitions Page is where the raw data and input for the project goes. Under Specific Project Names listed, put the parts of the project that need to be completed along with the needed steps for each project included. Then, in step 2, specify the life cycle steps for each part of the life cycle and be sure to make the titles of each part accurate. Step 3 requires the users to put the categories, though these should generally not be touched by the user. Finally, in step 4, the plan is specified, though again these should generally not be touched by the user" wrappingWidth="500.0">
